

The art of Guido Cantelli (23 CD)

A 23-disc box that gathered major recordings of Italian name conductor, Guido Cantelli [1920-1956]. Cantelli, a conductor of tragedy who was regarded as the successor of Toscanini and decided to take office as the young chief conductor of the Scala, but who finished his 36-year short life soon in an airplane accident. The entertainment was a cheerful and fresh one suitable for the new world after the war. Although the time of death was 1956, most of the recordings were monaural, but most of the recordings were session-recorded, there were lots of information volume with a lot of information volume, many of them had Brahms' symphonies No. 3, Beethoven Symphony No. 7, Schubert: incomplete, Mozart: Stereo recording such as Symphony No. 29 and so on, so I think that the viewing conditions are relatively good. (HMV)

